This paper deals with the computation of multi-valued partial CFL functions using pushdown automata, which falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The paper also involves combinatorial analysis, which suggests a possible fit under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DS). The use of colored automata and their simulation of pushdown automata may also suggest a connection to computational complexity theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper involves the study of stack histories, which could be related to programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO).
